description: Some 1.4 million Haitians are on the verge of famine, and more than 4 million require food aid, sometimes eating only once a day or not at all.

title: Keshon Gilbert's big night leads No. 7 Iowa State past No. 14 Baylor 76-62 in Big 12 semifinals
description: Keshon Gilbert had 20 points, seven rebounds and seven assists to lead seventh-ranked Iowa State to a 76-62 victory over No. 14 Baylor in the semifinals of the Big 12 Tournament.

title: Tominaga, Williams lead Nebraska past Indiana, 93-66 in Big Ten quarterfinals
description: Keisei Tominaga and Brice Williams each buried four 3-pointers and scored 23 points each to power third-seeded Nebraska to 93-66 quarterfinal romp past Indiana in the quarterfinals of the Big Ten Conference tournament.

title: Jets shutout the Ducks
description: WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) — Tyler Toffoli scored his first two goals since being traded to Winnipeg and Laurent Brossoit stopped 21 shots for his second shutout of the season in the Jets’ with a 6-0 win over the Anaheim Ducks on Friday night.

title: Kopitar scores twice and Talbot makes 28 saves as Kings blank Blackhawks 5-0
description: Anze Kopitar scored two of Los Angeles’ four goals in the first period, and the Kings beat the Chicago Blackhawks 5-0.

title: Antelope Valley was the college basketball team without a college. Its season has come to an end
description: The Antelope Valley men's basketball team is done after one of the stranger seasons in recent memory.

title: Jokic scores 31, Nuggets top Spurs 117-106 in front of record crowd in Texas' capital city
description: Nikola Jokic scored 31 points and the Denver Nuggets beat San Antonio 117-106 on Friday night in a game played in the Texas capital as the Spurs drew a record crowd in their bid to broaden their regional fan base.

title: Toffoli scores 2 goals, Brossoit gets 2nd shutout of season as Jets beat Ducks 6-0
description: Tyler Toffoli scored his first two goals since being traded to Winnipeg and Laurent Brossoit stopped 21 shots for his second shutout of the season in the Jets’ 6-0 win over the Anaheim Ducks.

title: No. 10 Marquette holds off Providence 79-68 to reach back-to-back Big East championship games
description: Kam Jones scored 23 points and Oso Ighodaro had 20 as No. 10 Marquette beat seventh-seeded Providence 79-68, withstanding a second-half surge by Devin Carter and advancing to the Big East Tournament championship game for the second straight year.

title: Zion Williamson scores 34, Pelicans top Clippers 112-104 to tighten race for No. 4 seed
description: Zion Williamson scored 34 points and the New Orleans Pelicans beat Los Angeles 112-104 on Friday night, pulling within two games of the Clippers for the No. 4 seed in the Western Conference.

title: Oregon beats No. 6 Arizona 67-59 to end Wildcats' Pac-12 Tournament reign
description: Jackson Shelstad scored 21 points, Jermaine Couisnard had 20 and Oregon shut down No. 6 Arizona for a 67-59 victory in the Pac-12 Tournaments semifinals.

title: Howard rallies to beat top-seeded Norfolk State in Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference semifinal 80-74
description: Marcus Dockery scored 19 points and the fourth-seeded Howard Bison rallied to upset top-seeded Norfolk State 80-74 in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference semifinals

title: Alabama basketball coach Nate Oats signs new contract, athletic director says
description: Alabama basketball coach Nate Oats has signed a new contract. Alabama athletic director Greg Byrne said Friday in a social media post that Oats’ contract will go before the school's Board of Trustees next week.

title: Alex Morgan has a late goal, leads San Diego past Gotham FC 1-0 in the Challenge Cup
description: Alex Morgan scored in the 88th minute and the San Diego Wave won the Challenge Cup with a 1-0 victory over Gotham FC Friday night in the National Women’s Soccer League.

title: Florida Atlantic tops North Texas 77-71 in American Athletic Conference quarterfinals
description: Vladislav Goldin scored 21 points to help lead the second-seeded Florida Atlantic Owls past North Texas 77-71 in the quarterfinals of the American Athletic Conference tournament

title: Freeman scores 24 as Akron holds off Ohio 65-62 in Mid-American Conference semifinal
description: Enrique Freeman scored 24 points to help lead second-seed Akron to a 65-62 victory over Ohio in the Mid-American Conference tournament semifinals.

title: Hubert Davis backs Pitt for NCAA Tournament, but loss to Tar Heels leaves Panthers in limbo
description: Now all Jeff Capel and his team can do is wait and hope. Pittsburgh had a chance to take a giant step toward an NCAA Tournament berth.

title: UConn coach Dan Hurley, irritated by a fan again, gets technical foul in Big East Tournament
description: UConn coach Dan Hurley got heated about a fan again Friday night. Moments after St. John’s counterpart Rick Pitino received a technical foul for shouting at officials in the Big East semifinals, Hurley was whistled for one during the same stoppage in play.

title: North Korea's Kim enjoys a Russian luxury limousine gifted by Putin as the two nations expand ties
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un's new ride is a Russian luxury limousine gifted by President Vladimir Putin.

title: Franz Wagner scores 19 points, Banchero adds 17 as Magic beat short-handed Raptors 113-103
description: TORONTO (AP) — Franz Wagner had 19 points, Paolo Banchero scored 11 of his 17 points in the third quarter and the Orlando Magic beat short-handed Toronto 113-103 on Friday night, handing the Raptors their season-worst sixth straight loss.

title: Miami beats Detroit to end a four-game losing streak
description: DETROIT (AP) — Bam Adebayo had 22 points and nine rebounds in 29 minutes, and the Miami Heat ended a four-game losing streak with a 108-95 victory over the Detroit Pistons Friday night.

title: 3B J.D. Davis agrees to $2.5 million, 1-year contract with the Oakland A's, AP source says
description: Third baseman J.D. Davis has agreed to a $2.5 million, one-year contract with the Oakland Athletics just days after he was released by San Francisco.

title: Hundreds of people in Mexico City stretch out for a 'mass nap' to commemorate World Sleep Day
description: Those walking through the milling streets of downtown Mexico City were greeted with a strange and sleepy sight.

title: Aggies turn in 2nd upset of SEC quarterfinals, downing No. 9 Kentucky 97-87
description: Wade Taylor IV scored 32 points as Texas A&M upset ninth-ranked Kentucky 97-87 for the second biggest upset of the Southeastern Conference Tournament quarterfinals.

title: Booker scores 21, Suns use balanced scoring and hold off 4th quarter rally to beat Hornets 107-96
description: Devin Booker led a balanced Phoenix attack with 21 points and 11 assists as the Suns defeated the Charlotte Hornets 107-96 for their fourth win in six games.

title: Fifth-seed Saint Peter stuns top-seed Quinnipiac, 62-60 in MAAC semifinals on last-second shot
description: Mouhamed Sow scored the game-winning layup as time expired as the fifth-seeded Saint Peter's Peacocks stunned the Quinnipiac Bobcats, 62-60 in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference semifinals

title: Adebayo has 22 points and nine rebounds as Heat end four-game losing streak with win over Pistons
description: Bam Adebayo had 22 points and nine rebounds in 29 minutes as the Miami Heat ended a four-game losing streak with a 108-95 win over the Detroit Pistons on Friday.

title: No. 13 Illinois rallies to beat Ohio State 77-74 in Big Ten Tournament quarterfinals
description: Terrence Shannon Jr. scored 28 points to help No. 13 Illinois overcome a 10-point second-half deficit and beat Ohio State 77-74 in the quarterfinals of the Big Ten Tournament.

title: Cryer helps No. 1 Houston ride big second half to 82-59 rout of No. 25 Texas Tech in Big 12 tourney
description: L.J. Cryer hit six 3-pointers and scored 20 points as top-ranked Houston used a big second half to rout No. 25 Texas Tech 82-59 in the semifinals of the Big 12 Tournament.

title: RJ Davis takes over as No. 4 UNC reaches ACC Tournament final by beating Pitt 72-65
description: RJ Davis scored a game-high 25 points as No. 4 North Carolina advanced to the final of the Atlantic Coast Conference Tournament by beating Pittsburgh 72-65.

title: Charges sign Hayden Hurst, the team's 2nd tight end addition in free agency
description: The Los Angeles Chargers added their second tight end during free agency with the signing of Hayden Hurst on Friday.

title: Top-ranked Iga Swiatek routs Ukraine's Marta Kostyuk 6-2, 6-1 to reach Indian Wells final
description: Top-ranked Iga Swiatek has routed Marta Kostyuk 6-2, 6-1 to reach the BNP Paribas Open final. Swiatek improved to 19-2 this year, with her match wins leading the WTA Tour.

title: University of Maryland lifts suspension on most fraternities and sororities amid hazing probe
description: The University of Maryland has lifted its suspension of most fraternities and sororities after an investigation into hazing and alcohol-related activities.

title: PGA Tour player directors encouraged to meet with Saudi backers of LIV Golf
description: Players on the PGA Tour board of directors are moving closer to meeting with the Saudi leader behind rival LIV Golf.

title: Northwest Indiana sheriff says 3 men dead after being shot
description: A sheriff says a shooting at a home in Northwest Indiana has left three men dead. Lake County Sheriff Oscar Martinez Jr. says police sent Friday afternoon to a home in Griffith found two men dead and a third in critical condition, all having suffered gunshot wounds.

title: NBA Cup may factor into playoff tiebreakers. And the league addresses a post-break scoring slowdown
description: Success in the NBA’s in-season tournament could factor into playoff tiebreakers as early as next season, the league told its teams in a memo Friday following meetings with the competition committee.

title: Newton leads No. 2 UConn past St. John's 95-90 and into first Big East title game since 2011
description: Tristen Newton had 25 points and nine assists as No. 2 UConn advanced to the Big East championship game with a rollicking 95-90 victory over St.

title: Saints add wide receivers Cedrick Wilson and Stanley Morgan in free agency
description: The New Orleans Saints have signed a pair of free-agent receivers. They agreed to a two-year contract with Cedrick Wilson and a one-year deal with Stanley Morgan.

title: Teen gets 40 years in prison for Denver house fire that killed 5 from Senegal
description: One of three teens charged with starting a house fire in Denver that killed five members of a Senegalese family has been sentenced to 40 years in prison.
